<refsynopsisdiv><title>&synp-tt;</title>
<cmdsynopsis><command>install-jbi-component</command>&synopsis-common;
<arg choice="opt">&Dash;&Dash;target <replaceable>target</replaceable></arg>
<arg choice="plain"><replaceable>filepath</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1><title>&desc-tt;</title>
<para>The <command>install-jbi-component</command> command installs a service
engine or binding component into the JBI environment. </para>
<para>This command is supported in remote mode only.</para>
</refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&opts-tt;</title>
<variablelist termlength="medium">&options-common;
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;target</option></term>
<listitem><para>Specifies the target on which you are installing the JBI component.
Valid values are<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><literal>server</literal>, which installs the JBI component
on the default server instance <literal>server</literal>. This is the default
value.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><replaceable>cluster_name</replaceable>, which installs the
JBI component on every server instance in the cluster.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><replaceable>instance_name</replaceable>, which installs the
JBI component on the named unclustered server instance</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist></para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&oper-tt;</title>
<variablelist termlength="medium">
<varlistentry><term><replaceable>filepath</replaceable></term><listitem><para>
The path to the archive file that contains the attributes of the JBI component.
</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&exam-tt;</title>
<example>
<title>Using the install-jbi-component command</title>
<para>The following command installs a JBI component.</para>
<screen>asadmin> <userinput>install-jbi-component --user admin2
--passwordfile passwords.txt --target server1 filepath</userinput>
Command install-jbi-component <?Pub Caret>executed successfully.</screen>
</example>
</refsect1>
